The Telegraph - Calcutta : Sports

 IFA to take up referee issue 

A STAFF REPORTER

Calcutta: The IFA has also joined the clubs voiced protest against ?biased? refereeing in the current National Football League. 

At the request of the affiliated units, the state body has decided to write to the All India Football Federation (AIFF) to allocate more efficient referees in the next National Football League. 

?We have requested secretary Subrata Dutta, who is also the vice-president of the AIFF, to take up the matter, and he has agreed to do that in the next meeting,? a source said. ?The clubs from the city suffered a lot this time because of biased refereeing,? he added. 




